<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900906-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>900906-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Xerox Corp.:   Small Copiers Introduced;   Guarantee Program Begun</HL><DATE>09/06/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5</SO><CO>   XRX</CO><IN>OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)</IN><LP>   Xerox Corp. said it introduced two small conveniencecopiers, increasing to nine the number of small copiers itsells.   The Stamford, Conn., company said the 5034 model is thefirst 50 Series small copier equipped with an automaticdocument handler that can invert originals to make copies onboth sides of a piece of paper. The copier, with a list priceof $9,100, will be sold through Xerox's own sales force.</LP><TEXT>   The other new copier, the 5011 R/E, can process 12 copiesa minute, accept originals as big as 11 inches by 17 inches,and reduce or enlarge in ratios of 65%, 75% and 130% of theoriginal, Xerox said. It will retail for $2,895.   Xerox also said it is initiating a &quot;total satisfactionguarantee&quot; program for its products. Under the program,customers who maintain their Xerox equipment under Xeroxauthorized service or warranty can get a replacement if theyare dissatisfied with the equipment. The program covers allXerox products for three years.</TEXT></DOC>